---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Wonderfilled, Inc."
  description="Meet the studio behind GiantLands, Emperor of the Cherokee, and some of the most ambitious transmedia worlds in development today. Founded by Stephen Erin Dinehart IV, who coined the term Narrative Designer in 2006."
>

  <div class="page-hero">
    <div class="page-hero-eyebrow">About the Studio</div>
    <h1 class="page-hero-title">Where <em>Myth</em><br>Meets Medium.</h1>
    <p class="page-hero-sub">25+ years building worlds at the intersection of story, game, and culture.</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Studio Overview -->
  <section class="inner-section" style="background: var(--ink2);">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <div class="section-eyebrow">The Studio</div>
        <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);">Wonderfilled, <em>Inc.</em></h2>
        <div class="about-stat-grid" style="margin-top: 3rem;">
          <div class="about-stat">
            <div class="stat-num">25+</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Years in Industry</div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-stat">
            <div class="stat-num">AAA</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Game Credits</div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-stat">
            <div class="stat-num">THEA</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Award Winner</div>
          </div>
          <div class="about-stat">
            <div class="stat-num">∞</div>
            <div class="stat-label">Worlds to Build</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>Wonderfilled, Inc. is a <strong>transmedia studio and publisher</strong> founded by Stephen Erin Dinehart IV — the designer who coined the term <strong>Narrative Designer</strong> in 2006 and helped define the discipline now standard across the industry.</p>
        <p>We are an independent studio with a singular purpose: to build worlds that endure. Not content mills, not IP farms — actual mythologies, designed with the depth of Tolkien and the commercial clarity of Lucasfilm.</p>
        <p>From AAA console titles to Super Nintendo World, from Angry Birds to themed entertainment at Evermore Park — the Wonderfilled pedigree spans every platform where story lives.</p>
        <p>Our properties are designed to transcend platform: <strong>games, novels, experiences, and theme parks</strong> that share one mythology. We operate at the frontier where <strong>ancient story meets emergent technology</strong>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Founder -->
  <section class="inner-section" style="background: var(--ink);">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Founder</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem); margin-bottom: 4rem;">Stephen Erin <em>Dinehart IV.</em></h2>
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <div style="
          width: 100%;
          aspect-ratio: 3/4;
          background: var(--ink3);
          border: 1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.1);
          display: flex;
          align-items: flex-end;
          padding: 2rem;
        ">
          <div>
            <p style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif; font-size:1.5rem; color:var(--gold); letter-spacing:0.1em;">Stephen Erin Dinehart IV</p>
            <p style="font-size:0.55rem; letter-spacing:0.2em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--text-body); margin-top:0.4rem;">Founder · Wonderfilled, Inc.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>Stephen Erin Dinehart IV is a narrative designer, author, academic, and founder of Wonderfilled, Inc. He <strong>coined the term "Narrative Designer"</strong> in 2006, establishing a role and methodology now practiced at every major studio in the industry.</p>
        <p>His work spans AAA game development, themed entertainment (THEA Award winner), academic research, and original IP creation. He has lectured at <strong>Harvard Business School</strong>, spoken at TEDxTransmedia Geneva, RiseUp Cairo, and the Bristol VR Lab.</p>
        <p>His original IPs — GiantLands, Tablet of Destinies, Emperor of the Cherokee — represent a 30-year vision for American and world mythology rendered through interactive and narrative media.</p>
        <p><strong>Selected Credits:</strong></p>
        <p style="font-size:1rem; color:var(--text-body);">Super Nintendo World · Angry Birds (Rovio) · Evermore Park · Stage11 (David Guetta, Snoop Dogg) · The Dungeon Hobbyshop Museum · TEAAS Research</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Philosophy -->
  <section class="inner-section" style="background: var(--ink2);">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Philosophy</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem); margin-bottom: 3rem;">The Frontier <em>Principle.</em></h2>
    <div style="max-width: 800px;">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>We believe the studios of the future are also the <strong>guardians of myth</strong>. The most durable intellectual properties are not products — they are living mythologies, with internal logic, sacred geography, and the kind of emotional truth that survives format changes.</p>
        <p>We operate at the frontier where <strong>ancient story meets emergent technology</strong>. That means using AI and synthetic media thoughtfully — not as a replacement for human craft, but as an extension of it. It means designing for the age of infinite narrative, where your audience inhabits your world rather than consuming it.</p>
        <p>It also means having the courage to build slow. <strong>TSR had the Dragon. Lucasfilm had the Ranch. Wonderfilled has a plan.</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="background: var(--ink); text-align: center; padding: 8rem 4rem;">
    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="justify-content: center;">Partner With Us</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 5rem); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Let's Build <em>Together.</em></h2>
    <p style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 300; font-style: italic; color: var(--mist2); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; line-height: 1.6;">
      Whether you're a studio, publisher, park, or storyteller — we want to hear about your world.
    </p>
    <a class="btn-primary" href="/contact">Get in Touch</a>
  </section>

</Base>
